  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "AutoCAD Draughtsman",
  "description": "<p></p><h2><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Create and modify 2D drawings and 3D models using AutoCAD and Autodesk Inventor</p></li><li><p>Design and develop advanced assembly and packaging concepts for industrial fiber optic products, SiPM (Silicon Photomultiplier) sensors, and Time of Flight (TOF) sensor packaging</p></li><li><p>Perform optomechanical integration by creating complex 3D models and 2D manufacturing drawings for optical sub-assemblies, sensors, and final products</p></li><li><p>Support New Product Introduction (NPI) activities by preparing preliminary drawings and technical documentation</p></li><li><p>Update and revise existing drawings in accordance with Engineering Change Orders (ECOs)</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate and well-organized drawing databases in compliance with ISO documentation standards</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with engineers to ensure drawings meet design, manufacturing, and quality requirements</p></li><li><p>Provide drafting and design support during production and engineering reviews</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Qualifications</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Minimum Diploma in Mechanical Engineering or related technical discipline</p></li><li><p>Minimum 1 year of experience in the semiconductor industry</p></li><li><p>Experience in fiber optics or optical communication is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Autodesk Inventor 2026 and AutoCAD 2026</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of Geometric Dimensioning & Tolerancing (GD&T) in accordance with ISO/ASME standards</p></li><li><p>Familiar with NPI and production processes, including Bill of Materials (BOM) and Engineering Change Orders (ECO)</p></li><li><p>High level of attention to detail and accuracy</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and meet tight production timelines</p></li></ul><p><p><br /><br /><strong>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</strong></p><p>Brunel International S.E.A Pte. Ltd.</p><p>UEN No: 199603098R</p><p>EA License No: 16S8067</p><p>Shahidan Yusof - R1658969</p></p>",
